values:
So, it has been about five months since i've joined the Mac occult.&nbsp; I felt MANY mixed feelings for a very long time about making the switch.&nbsp; I know that the Mac is overpriced, in so far as the amount of memory and storage etc. compared to the market price of comparable pcs.&nbsp; My last computer was a Dell with XP.&nbsp; After trying to navigate vista on my parents computer and getting completely angered with it as it is as a counter-intuitive frustration device, i decided that anything would be better than this.&nbsp; If i were a bit more savvy, i'm sure i would have opted for a linux operating pc.&nbsp; 

So i feel this growing guilt that i'm paying for the sleek ads Mac puts on tv.&nbsp; I guess i hate the idea of paying for a brand, in whatever context.&nbsp; I don't wear brand clothing that self advertises.&nbsp; However, i am quite fond of adapting simplicity in my life.&nbsp; And Macs are that.&nbsp; I don't know that i've sworn out of frustration in the failure to perform even once since i've had my lovely.&nbsp; 

But like a tatoo, people adorn themselves with the bitten apple logo as though it might imbue their lives with beauty and simplicity.&nbsp; Counter-intuitively the Mac suggests that More is Less.&nbsp; That our lives will begin once we have the latest gadget.&nbsp;

Sometimes i worry that i don't feel things the way i'm supposed to.&nbsp; I feel like everything that is beautiful sort of skips over me, like water over a duck.&nbsp; I get the sense of what it is i should feel, but it doesn't resonate with me the way it is "supposed" to.&nbsp; 

When i go to hear music, or go to art shows, or see sunsets or see babies, or taste chocolate or wine, i can't escape this feeling that i am somehow experiencing a numbed version and everybody else is experiencing the real deal.&nbsp; People are brought to tears by the arts because it touches them so deeply.&nbsp; So i feel like i'm supposed to fake it.&nbsp; I'm supposed to say how wonderful everything is when in reality it wasn't even bad enough for me to hate it strongly, passionately.&nbsp; It's just sort of there.

I guess it's funny that i'm in the arts then.&nbsp; When i really don't care about art at all.&nbsp; How can you make yourself care?&nbsp; Where does caring come from?&nbsp; Maybe all of my interest in art has come from my recognition that making art objects moves other people in ways i will never be moved, which in turn moves me to a lesser degree.&nbsp; From the first shitty drawing that wound up on mom's fridge, i've been making things to try to feel some trickle down of passion ignited in others.&nbsp; But chances are, mom was just trying to be nice and she thought your drawing was crap but she loved you.&nbsp; 

Maybe we are all lying to spare each other.&nbsp; We are all happily gobbling up crap and calling it candy because life without passion is worse that admitting we're eating shit.
